		},
		{
			"name":"Countermeasures",
			"type":"feature",
			"img":"icons/svg/cancel.svg",
			"system":{
				"description":{
					"value":"<ul><li><b>Athletics DC 6 or Athletics (without a running start) DC 11:</b> A character who makes a successful check can jump over a single pressure plate square.</li><li><b>Thievery DC 27:</b> An adjacent character can disable a trigger plate with a successful check.</li><li><b>Thievery DC 22:</b> A creature adjacent to the control panel can disable the entire trap with a successful check.</li><li><b>Dungeoneering DC 20:</b> A successful check grants the party a +2 bonus to Thievery checks to delay or disable the trap.</li><li>A character can ready an action to attack the spears (AC 13, other defenses 10; hp 10). When the spears in one square are destroyed, that trigger plate becomes useless.</li><li>A character can attack a trigger plate or the control panel (AC 12, other defenses 10; hp 30; resist 5 all). Destroying a trigger plate renders it useless, and destroying the control panel disables the entire trap.</li></ul>",
